purpose.p:
     The   module enables the representation of:


data that identify documents () and versions of documents (); 

assignments of documentation () to product or activity data, or to assign sections of documents to product or activity data () ;

document version in a digital () or physical format (); 

relationships between files () or document definitions ()

assignment of properties to a particular representation of a document version or a file ();

digital files () stored on an electronic storage device or non-digital hardcopies ().

The   unit of functionality module addresses the requirements to define a document, and relate all or parts of the document to a product design, or , including product variants, tasks, and other documents.  A document is defined as a body of information or data that can be packaged for delivery on a single medium.  
     Some examples of documents are: 


drawings; 

reports; 

standards; 

databases; 

application software; 

engineering drawings; 

CAD models; 

computer file reports; 

video clips; 

tapes.

